Let's think step by step: A full circle with radius 18 has circumference $2(\pi)(18)=36\pi$, so a 300-degree sector has arc length (shown in blue below) \[\frac{300^\circ}{360^\circ}\cdot 36\pi = 30\pi.\][asy]
